Scenarios of tennant payment
----------------------------------------
Payment Scenarios:

1. Normal Payment (before due date/‡∏à‡πà‡∏≤‡∏¢‡∏õ‡∏Å‡∏ï‡∏¥)
    code logic need: 
    - Regular bill amount
    - Status change to "paid"

2. No Payment (not futher than overdue/‡∏ö‡∏¥‡∏•‡∏õ‡∏Å‡∏ï‡∏¥‡∏ó‡∏µ‡πà‡∏¢‡∏±‡∏á‡πÑ‡∏°‡πà‡∏à‡πà‡∏≤‡∏¢‡πÅ‡∏ï‡πà‡∏¢‡∏±‡∏á‡πÑ‡∏°‡πà‡πÄ‡∏•‡∏¢‡∏Å‡∏≥‡∏´‡∏ô‡∏î)
    code logic need:
    - Regular bill amount
    - Status changes to "unpaid"

3. Overdue Payment (‡πÄ‡∏Å‡∏¥‡∏ô‡∏Å‡∏≥‡∏´‡∏ô‡∏î‡∏à‡πà‡∏≤‡∏¢)
    code logic need:
    - Status changes to "overdue" after due date
    - Track days overdue
    - Regular bill amount
    - Late fee not appiled (if not futher than 5 days)
    - Late fee applies (caculate by days after due date)
    
  
4. Payment Extension (‡∏Ç‡∏≠‡πÄ‡∏•‡∏∑‡πà‡∏≠‡∏ô‡∏ß‡∏±‡∏ô‡∏à‡πà‡∏≤‡∏¢)
    code logic need:
    - New due date for that month
    - Status changes to "Extend Approved" after due date
    - Note explaining extension
    - May or may not include late fee (based on agreement)

5. Rent Discount (‡∏Ç‡∏≠‡∏à‡πà‡∏≤‡∏¢‡πÄ‡∏î‡∏∑‡∏≠‡∏ô‡∏ñ‡∏±‡∏î‡πÑ‡∏õ)
    code logic need:
    - New due date for that month
    - Status changes to "Extend to Next Month" 
    - Add total to next month bill
    - Note explaining Reason (who approved/verified)

6. Additional Charges (‡∏ñ‡πâ‡∏≤‡∏°‡∏µ‡πÑ‡∏£‡∏û‡∏±‡∏á‡πÅ‡∏•‡πâ‡∏ß‡πÄ‡∏Ç‡∏≤‡∏ï‡πâ‡∏≠‡∏á‡∏à‡πà‡∏≤‡∏¢‡∏Ñ‡πà‡∏≤‡∏ã‡πà‡∏≠‡∏°)
    code logic need:
    - Regular bill amount
    - Extra charges (with description)
    - Final total

7. Multiple Month Issue (‡∏Ñ‡πâ‡∏≤‡∏á‡∏¢‡∏≠‡∏î‡πÄ‡∏î‡∏∑‡∏≠‡∏ô‡∏ó‡∏µ‡πà‡πÅ‡∏•‡πâ‡∏ß‡∏î‡πâ‡∏ß‡∏¢)
    code logic need:
    - Add Previous months to bill
    - Accumulated late fees
    - Payment allocation order (In case tenant pay only 1 bill)
    
Payment Method:
    Bank Transfer
    Promptpay
    Cash

